<section id="home">
  <div id="home_parallalax">
    <div class="vertical-center">
      <h1>#ManaTelugu ManaBrindavanam❤</h1>
      <p>Brindavanam is a Telugu cultural association uniting all the Telugu speaking community. Being the largest assoc on the campus and  passing the "Telugu" bond over the years.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row ">
      <div class="col-lg-12 aboutus">
        <h1>About us</h1>
        <p>
          Brindavanam is the Telugu regional assoc,  in a vastly diverse campus with people from all over the country speaking every language imaginable we aim to create a space so that our cinema, our culture and our festivals will be celebrated! Right from blowing the roof off the auditorium during a Telugu movie screening, jamming to Gaallo Telinattunde and Rooba Rooba in our Nescafe lawns, getting all the serious film buffs together and quizzing them on Tollywood trivia to gathering around the Bhogi fire at 6:00 AM. We aim to do it all to make living on campus feel that much closer to being at home❤
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="graycol">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Events</h1>
      <div class="row eventRow">

        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 details">
          <div class=" eventCards event1">
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
            <p><strong>Freshers:</strong>
Your first chance at being a part of the family. An annual event specifically for the incoming batch where you get to know fellow Telugu people. A night filled with energy,fun and more fun. Also a special video welcoming the freshers and hence officially marking the beginning of your campus journey ;P</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 ">
          <div class=" eventCards event2">

          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
            <p><strong>Sankranti Celebrations:</strong>
Revisit our childhood favourites with Bhogi Bonfire early in the morning and Rangoli competition and Kite festival and more exciting events to follow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 "><div class=" eventCards event3"></div>
        <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
          <p><strong>Tollywood Quiz:</strong>
Do you think you're that so called "movie buff"? Do you live and breathe Telugu cinema? Then this is definitely for you. What better way to celebrate our culture than discussing about cinema. Welcome to the night filled with "Telugu ness" and crazy Tolly trivia,not to mention the exciting prizes..It's a quiz after all.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      </div>

      <div class="row eventRow">
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 ">
          <div class=" eventCards event4">
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
            <p><strong>Cultural Night:</strong>
That one special night where we embrace our culture filled with varied performances to showcase your talent. Get dressed , get clicked with your homies , Eat delicious Telugu food , Enjoy your hearts out and make memories that last forever.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 ">
          <div class=" eventCards event5">

          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
            <p><strong>Gnapika:</strong>
 Arguably,we live the best days of our lives on campus. This is an outlet for the passout batch to revisit those beautiful moments and memories made along the way along with your friends. Relive the entire campus life in oneday.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6 "><div class=" eventCards event6"></div>
        <div class="col-lg-12 reveal1">
          <p><strong>Telugu DJ Night:</strong>
Take your energy levels to the peaks unknown to you earlier. Dance with all your energy  for our Telugu songs, with a mix of DJ till you drain all the energy out. The night is ours.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
